===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} ''[[asken#Middle English|asken]]'' from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|ascian|āscian, āxian|to ask|lang=ang}} from {{proto|Germanic|aiskōjanan|to ask|lang=en}} from {{proto|Germanic|ayǝs-|to look for|lang=en}}.  Akin to {{etyl|ofs|-}} ''[[ascian#Old Frisian|āscian]]'' "to ask", {{etyl|osx|-}} ''[[eiskon#Old Saxon|ēskon, ēscian]]'' "to demand" ({{etyl|nl|-}} ''[[eisen#Dutch|eisen]]'' "to demand, require"), {{etyl|goh|-}} ''[[eiscon#Old High German|eiscōn]]'' "to demand, ask" ({{etyl|de|-}} {{term|heischen|lang=de}} "to demand"), {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|æske|lang=da}}, {{etyl|rus|-}} {{term|искать|tr=iskat'|lang=ru}}.

